! Nested Clusters

Clusters can be nested inside other clusters. Drag one cluster container onto another to nest them.

<div style="height:450px;overflow:hidden;">
<$graph>
<$properties $for="graph" clusterData="$:/state/demo/nested-clusters">
<$properties $for="nodes" color="SteelBlue" size="15">

  <$node $tiddler="nc:alice" label="Alice"/>
  <$node $tiddler="nc:bob" label="Bob"/>
  <$node $tiddler="nc:carol" label="Carol"/>
  <$node $tiddler="nc:dave" label="Dave"/>
  <$node $tiddler="nc:eve" label="Eve"/>
  <$node $tiddler="nc:frank" label="Frank"/>

  <$edge $from="nc:alice" $to="nc:bob"/>
  <$edge $from="nc:bob" $to="nc:carol"/>
  <$edge $from="nc:carol" $to="nc:dave"/>
  <$edge $from="nc:dave" $to="nc:eve"/>
  <$edge $from="nc:eve" $to="nc:frank"/>

</$properties>
</$properties>
</$graph>
</div>

!! Try it

# Drag ''Alice'' onto ''Bob'' → creates "Cluster #1"
# Drag ''Carol'' onto ''Dave'' → creates "Cluster #2"
# Drag ''Cluster #1'' onto ''Cluster #2'' → nests #1 inside #2
# Double-click cluster labels to rename (e.g. "Frontend" inside "Engineering")
# Pick different colors for outer and inner clusters

!! Rules

* Circular nesting is blocked (can't nest A inside B if B is already inside A)
* Dragging a cluster far away from its parent cluster removes the nesting
* Empty clusters auto-delete when their last member is removed
